{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Reproduction Steps\n1. Push any commit to `main` (or open a PR).\n2. The `verify-identity` GitHub Actions workflow (`.github/workflows/verify-identity.yaml`) runs the authenticated-authorship merge-gate.\n3. The job fails.\n\n**Expected:** the gate runs and does not block a landing when the project has not opted into enforcement.\n\n**Actual (before fix):** the step exits 2 with `ticket store not found at '.../.tickets-tracker' (infrastructure issue — the tickets store is not mounted; not an authorship problem)`.\n\n## Root Cause\nTwo compounding problems:\n1. The workflow did a plain `actions/checkout@v5` and never mounted the `tickets` orphan branch (the store lives at the gitignored `.tickets-tracker/` worktree), so the gate exited 2.\n2. The workflow forced `--require-authenticated` with no grandfather boundary, while the store holds **0 signed / 3504 unsigned** events (write-signing was scaffolded but never rolled out). So even with the store mounted the gate would fail every push by construction.\n\n## Fix (delivered)\nEnforcement posture is driven by project config, with all pre-rollout events grandfathered:\n- Mount the `tickets` branch as `.tickets-tracker` before the gating step (mirrors `reconcile-bridge.yml`).\n- Drop the forced `--require-authenticated`/`--since` flags; the gate now honours `identity.require_authenticated` (kept OFF ⇒ advisory, exit 0) and `identity.enforce_since` (grandfather boundary) from `rebar.toml`.\n- Set `identity.enforce_since` to the tracker HEAD at rollout-prep so, when signing is later enabled and the flag flipped, historical unsigned events are grandfathered and only new signed writes are enforced.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `.github/workflows/verify-identity.yaml` mounts the `tickets` orphan branch as `.tickets-tracker` (full fetch + `git worktree add -B tickets .tickets-tracker origin/tickets`) before the `verify-identity (gating)` step, and the checkout uses `fetch-depth: 0`.\n- [ ] The gating step invokes `rebar verify-identity` with **no** forced `--require-authenticated`/`--since` flags, so posture follows config.\n- [ ] `rebar.toml` has an `[identity]` block with `require_authenticated = false` and `enforce_since` pinned to a tracker-branch ref (grandfather boundary).\n- [ ] [operator-attested] The `verify-identity` workflow run on `main` after this change lands shows a green (success) conclusion. Evidence: the GitHub Actions run URL + its `success` conclusion recorded as a comment."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1783980007977972001,"uuid":"3bc70f4d-b909-439d-b525-acc04dd3de56"}